        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 3:51PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 351 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 12 miles northeast of Westplains to 9
miles north of Stoneham, or extending from 20 miles southeast of
Kimball to 27 miles west of Sterling, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling, Merino, Iliff, Peetz, North Sterling Reservoir, Logan
Corners, Padroni, Atwood, Pawnee Pass, Westplains, Willard and
Proctor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

If on North Sterling Reservoir, get out of the water and secure
loose items. Boaters can expect strong gusty winds and locally
higher waves. Boaters should seek safe harbor immediately.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
